Building
########

material model laboratory (matmodlab) is an object oriented model driver. The
majority of the source code is written in Python and requires no additional
building. Many of the material models, however, are written in Fortran and
require a seperate compile step.


System Requirements
===================

*matmodlab* has been built and tested extensively on several versions of linux
and the Apple Mac OSX 10.8 operating systems.


Required Software
=================

*matmodlab* requires the following software installed for your platform:

#) `Python 2.7 <http://www.python.org/>`_ or newer

#) `NumPy 1.8 <http://www.numpy.org/>`_ or newer

#) `SciPy 0.13 <http://www.scipy.org/>`_ or newer

*matmodlab* is developed and tested using the `Enthought <http://http://www.enthought.com/>`_ *Python distribution*.

Optional Software
=================

#) Fortran compiler


.. _installation:

Installation
============

#) Make sure that all *matmodlab* prerequisites are installed and working properly.

#) Add ``toolset`` to your ``PATH`` environment variable

#) [Optional] Set the ``MMLMTLS`` environment variable to point to directories
   containing additional material models (user developed, not part of *matmodlab*).

#) run::

        % PYTHON setup.py build_all

   where ``PYTHON`` is the python interpreter that has *NumPy* and *SciPy*
   installed. :file:`setup.py` will build materials, and optional fortran utilities
   and write the following executable scripts::

       GMD_ROOT
         toolset/
           buildmtls
           mmd
           exdiff
           exdump
           mml
           mmv
           runtests

Testing the Installation
========================

To test *matmodlab* after installation, execute::

	% runtests -k fast $tests_dir

which will run the "fast" tests found in $tests_dir directory.

To run the full test suite execute::

	% runtests [-jN] $tests_dir

Please note that running all of the tests takes several minutes.


Troubleshooting
===============

If you experience problems when building/installing/testing *matmodlab*, you
can ask help from `Tim Fuller <tjfulle@sandia.gov>`_. Please include the
following information in your message:

#) Platform information OS, its distribution name and version information etc.::

        % PYTHON -c 'import os,sys;print os.name,sys.platform'
	% uname -a


#) Information about C,C++,Fortran compilers/linkers as reported by
   the compilers when requesting their version information, e.g.,
   the output of::

        % gcc -v
        % gfortran --version

#) Python version::

        % PYTHON -c 'import sys;print sys.version'

#) *NumPy* version::

        % PYTHON -c 'import numpy;print numpy.__version__'

#) *SciPy* version::

        % PYTHON -c 'import scipy;print scipy.__version__'

#) Feel free to add any other relevant information.
